# Linux Fundamentals

## Overview

Linux is one of the most widely used operating systems in servers, cloud environments, cybersecurity, and web application infrastructure. Understanding Linux fundamentals is essential for system administration, network security, and web penetration testing.

---

# 1. Linux File System Structure

Linux organizes files using a hierarchical directory structure that starts from the root directory:

```text
/
├── home
├── root
├── etc
├── var
├── usr
├── tmp
```

### Important Directories

| Directory | Purpose                             |
| --------- | ----------------------------------- |
| /home     | User files and personal directories |
| /root     | Home directory of the root user     |
| /etc      | System configuration files          |
| /var      | Logs and variable data              |
| /usr      | Installed applications and binaries |
| /tmp      | Temporary files                     |

### Commands Practiced

```bash
pwd
ls
cd
cd ..
cd /
```

### Lessons Learned

* Linux uses a hierarchical file system.
* The root directory `/` is the starting point of the entire system.
* Users typically work inside `/home/username`.

