# 3. Permissions & Ownership

Linux controls access through permissions.

### Permission Types

| Permission | Meaning |
| ---------- | ------- |
| r          | Read    |
| w          | Write   |
| x          | Execute |

Example:

```text
-rw-r--r--
```

### Understanding chmod

```bash
chmod 777 file.txt
chmod 644 file.txt
chmod 600 secret.txt
```

### Common Permission Values

| Value | Meaning                                    |
| ----- | ------------------------------------------ |
| 777   | Full access for everyone                   |
| 755   | Full owner access, read/execute for others |
| 644   | Owner read/write, others read only         |
| 600   | Owner only                                 |

### Lessons Learned

* Incorrect permissions can create security risks.
* Sensitive files should use restrictive permissions.

