# 7. SSH Fundamentals

SSH provides secure remote access.

### Verify SSH Client

```bash
ssh -V
which ssh
```

### Install SSH Server

```bash
sudo apt install openssh-server
```

### Service Management

```bash
systemctl status ssh
sudo systemctl start ssh
sudo systemctl enable ssh
```

### Local SSH Connection

```bash
ssh tarig@localhost
```

### Lessons Learned

* SSH encrypts communication.
* SSH is the standard protocol for Linux server administration.
* Port 22 is the default SSH port.

