# 8. Networking Commands

### View Network Interfaces

```bash
ip a
```

### View Routing Table

```bash
ip route
```

### Display IP Address

```bash
hostname -I
```

### Test Connectivity

```bash
ping 127.0.0.1
ping google.com
```

### DNS Lookup

```bash
nslookup google.com
```

### View Listening Ports

```bash
ss -tuln
```

### Lessons Learned

* Every device requires an IP address.
* DNS translates domain names into IP addresses.
* Open ports reveal running services.

