# 9. Log Analysis

Linux stores logs inside:

```text
/var/log
```

### Important Logs

| File     | Purpose                 |
| -------- | ----------------------- |
| auth.log | Authentication events   |
| syslog   | General system logs     |
| dmesg    | Kernel messages         |
| dpkg.log | Package management logs |

### Commands Practiced

View recent log entries:

```bash
sudo tail /var/log/auth.log
```

Login history:

```bash
last
```

### Lessons Learned

* Logs are critical for troubleshooting and security investigations.
* Authentication logs help identify login activity.

