# 10. Text Processing

### grep

Search inside files:

```bash
grep admin users.txt
```

### head

Display first lines:

```bash
head users.txt
```

### tail

Display last lines:

```bash
tail users.txt
```

### wc

Count lines and words:

```bash
wc users.txt
wc -l users.txt
```

### sort

Sort file contents:

```bash
sort users.txt
```

### Lessons Learned

* Text-processing tools are essential for log analysis.
* grep is one of the most frequently used Linux commands in cybersecurity.

